{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_b0f542659d9c439e80491c00","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t<h1 align=\"center\">\n2\t  <img src=\"https://github.com/embeddings-benchmark/mteb/blob/main/docs/images/logos/mteb_logo/dots-icon.png?raw=true\" alt=\"MTEB\" width=\"28\" style=\"vertical-align: middle; margin-right: 10px;\"/> MTEB\n3\t</h1>\n4\t\n5\t<h3 align=\"center\" style=\"border-bottom: none;\">Multimodal toolbox for evaluating embeddings and retrieval systems</h3>\n6\t\n7\t<p align=\"center\">\n8\t    <a href=\"https://github.com/embeddings-benchmark/mteb/releases\">\n9\t        <img alt=\"GitHub release\" src=\"https://img.shields.io/github/release/embeddings-benchmark/mteb.svg\">\n10\t    </a>\n11\t    <a href=\"https://github.com/embeddings-benchmark/mteb/blob/master/LICENSE\">\n12\t        <img alt=\"License\" src=\"https://img.shields.io/github/license/embeddings-benchmark/mteb.svg?color=green\">\n13\t    </a>\n14\t    <a href=\"https://pepy.tech/project/mteb\">\n15\t        <img alt=\"Downloads\" src=\"https://static.pepy.tech/personalized-badge/mteb?period=total&units=international_system&left_color=grey&right_color=orange&left_text=Downloads\">\n16\t    </a>\n17\t</p>\n18\t\n19\t<h4 align=\"center\">\n20\t    <p>\n21\t        <a href=\"https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/installation/\">Installation</a> |\n22\t        <a href=\"https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/\">Usage</a> |\n23\t        <a href=\"https://huggingface.co/spaces/mteb/leaderboard\">Leaderboard</a> |\n24\t        <a href=\"https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/\">Documentation</a> |\n25\t        <a href=\"#citing\">Citing</a>\n26\t    </p>\n27\t</h4>\n28\t\n29\t\n30\t<h3 align=\"center\">\n31\t    <a href=\"https://huggingface.co/spaces/mteb/leaderboard\"><img style=\"float: middle; padding: 10px 10px 10px 10px;\" width=\"60\" height=\"55\" src=\"https://github.com/embeddings-benchmark/mteb/blob/main/docs/images/logos/hf_logo.png?raw=true\" /></a>\n32\t</h3>\n33\t\n34\t\n35\t## Installation\n36\t\n37\tYou can install mteb simply using pip or uv. For more on installation please see the [documentation](https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/installation/).\n38\t\n39\t```bash\n40\tpip install mteb\n41\t```\n42\t\n43\tFor faster installation, you can also use [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/):\n44\t```bash\n45\tuv add mteb\n46\t```\n47\t\n48\t\n49\t## Example Usage\n50\t\n51\tBelow we present a simple use-case example. For more information, see the [documentation](https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/).\n52\t\n53\t```python\n54\timport mteb\n55\tfrom sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer\n56\t\n57\t# Select model\n58\tmodel_name = \"sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2\"\n59\tmodel = mteb.get_model(model_name) # if the model is not implemented in MTEB it will be eq. to SentenceTransformer(model_name)\n60\t\n61\t# Select tasks\n62\ttasks = mteb.get_tasks(tasks=[\"Banking77Classification.v2\"])\n63\t\n64\t# evaluate\n65\tresults = mteb.evaluate(model, tasks=tasks)\n66\t```\n67\t\n68\tYou can also run it using the CLI:\n69\t\n70\t```bash\n71\tmteb run \\\n72\t    -m sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2 \\\n73\t    -t \"Banking77Classification.v2\" \\\n74\t    --output-folder results\n75\t```\n76\t\n77\tFor more on how to use the CLI check out the [related documentation](https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/get_started/usage/cli/).\n78\t\n79\t## Overview\n80\t\n81\t| Overview                       |                                                                                      |\n82\t|--------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n83\t| 📈 [Leaderboard]               | The interactive leaderboard of the benchmark                                         |\n84\t| **Get Started**.               |                                                                                      |\n85\t| 🏃 [Get Started]               | Overview of how to use mteb                                                          |\n86\t| 🤖 [Defining Models]           | How to use existing model and define custom ones                                     |\n87\t| 📋 [Selecting tasks]           | How to select tasks, benchmarks, splits etc.                                         |\n88\t| 🏭 [Running Evaluation]        | How to run the evaluations, including cache management, speeding up evaluations etc. |\n89\t| 📊 [Loading Results]           | How to load and work with existing model results                                     |\n90\t| **Overview**.                  |                                                                                      |\n91\t| 📋 [Tasks]                     | Overview of available tasks                                                          |\n92\t| 📐 [Benchmarks]                | Overview of available benchmarks                                                     |\n93\t| 🤖 [Models]                    | Overview of available Models                                                         |\n94\t| **Contributing**               |                                                                                      |\n95\t| 🤖 [Adding a model]            | How to submit a model to MTEB and to the leaderboard                                 |\n96\t| 👩‍💻 [Adding a dataset]          | How to add a new task/dataset to MTEB                                                |\n97\t| 👩‍💻 [Adding a benchmark]        | How to add a new benchmark to MTEB and to the leaderboard                            |\n98\t| 🤝 [Contributing]              | How to contribute to MTEB and set it up for development                              |\n99\t\n100\t[Get Started]: https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/\n101\t[Defining Models]: https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/get_started/usage/defining_the_model/\n102\t[Selecting tasks]: https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/get_started/usage/selecting_tasks/\n103\t[Running Evaluation]: https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/get_started/usage/running_the_evaluation/\n104\t[Loading Results]: https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/get_started/usage/loading_results/\n105\t[Tasks]: https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/overview/available_tasks/retrieval/\n106\t[Benchmarks]: https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/overview/available_benchmarks/\n107\t[Models]: https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/overview/available_models/text/\n108\t[Contributing]: https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/CONTRIBUTING/\n109\t[Adding a model]: https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/contributing/adding_a_model/\n110\t[Adding a dataset]: https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/contributing/adding_a_dataset/\n111\t[Adding a benchmark]: https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/contributing/adding_a_benchmark/\n112\t[Leaderboard]: https://huggingface.co/spaces/mteb/leaderboard\n113\t\n114\t## Citing\n115\t\n116\tMTEB was introduced in \"[MTEB: Massive Text Embedding Benchmark](https://arxiv.org/abs/2210.07316)\", and heavily expanded in \"[MMTEB: Massive Multilingual Text Embedding Benchmark](https://arxiv.org/abs/2502.13595)\". When using `mteb`, we recommend that you cite both articles.\n117\t\n118\t<details>\n119\t  <summary> Bibtex Citation (click to unfold) </summary>\n120\t\n121\t\n122\t```bibtex\n123\t@article{muennighoff2022mteb,\n124\t  author = {Muennighoff, Niklas and Tazi, Nouamane and Magne, Loïc and Reimers, Nils},\n125\t  title = {MTEB: Massive Text Embedding Benchmark},\n126\t  publisher = {arXiv},\n127\t  journal={arXiv preprint arXiv:2210.07316},\n128\t  year = {2022},\n129\t  url = {https://arxiv.org/abs/2210.07316},\n130\t  doi = {10.48550/ARXIV.2210.07316},\n131\t}\n132\t\n133\t@article{enevoldsen2025mmtebmassivemultilingualtext,\n134\t  title={MMTEB: Massive Multilingual Text Embedding Benchmark},\n135\t  author={Kenneth Enevoldsen and Isaac Chung and Imene Kerboua and Márton Kardos and Ashwin Mathur and David Stap and Jay Gala and Wissam Siblini and Dominik Krzemiński and Genta Indra Winata and Saba Sturua and Saiteja Utpala and Mathieu Ciancone and Marion Schaeffer and Gabriel Sequeira and Diganta Misra and Shreeya Dhakal and Jonathan Rystrøm and Roman Solomatin and Ömer Çağatan and Akash Kundu and Martin Bernstorff and Shitao Xiao and Akshita Sukhlecha and Bhavish Pahwa and Rafał Poświata and Kranthi Kiran GV and Shawon Ashraf and Daniel Auras and Björn Plüster and Jan Philipp Harries and Loïc Magne and Isabelle Mohr and Mariya Hendriksen and Dawei Zhu and Hippolyte Gisserot-Boukhlef and Tom Aarsen and Jan Kostkan and Konrad Wojtasik and Taemin Lee and Marek Šuppa and Crystina Zhang and Roberta Rocca and Mohammed Hamdy and Andrianos Michail and John Yang and Manuel Faysse and Aleksei Vatolin and Nandan Thakur and Manan Dey and Dipam Vasani and Pranjal Chitale and Simone Tedeschi and Nguyen Tai and Artem Snegirev and Michael Günther and Mengzhou Xia and Weijia Shi and Xing Han Lù and Jordan Clive and Gayatri Krishnakumar and Anna Maksimova and Silvan Wehrli and Maria Tikhonova and Henil Panchal and Aleksandr Abramov and Malte Ostendorff and Zheng Liu and Simon Clematide and Lester James Miranda and Alena Fenogenova and Guangyu Song and Ruqiya Bin Safi and Wen-Ding Li and Alessia Borghini and Federico Cassano and Hongjin Su and Jimmy Lin and Howard Yen and Lasse Hansen and Sara Hooker and Chenghao Xiao and Vaibhav Adlakha and Orion Weller and Siva Reddy and Niklas Muennighoff},\n136\t  publisher = {arXiv},\n137\t  journal={arXiv preprint arXiv:2502.13595},\n138\t  year={2025},\n139\t  url={https://arxiv.org/abs/2502.13595},\n140\t  doi = {10.48550/arXiv.2502.13595},\n141\t}\n142\t```\n143\t</details>\n144\t\n145\t\n146\tIf you use any of the specific benchmarks, we also recommend that you cite the authors of both the benchmark and its tasks:\n147\t\n148\t```py\n149\tbenchmark = mteb.get_benchmark(\"MTEB(eng, v2)\")\n150\tbenchmark.citation # get citation for a specific benchmark\n151\t\n152\t# you can also create a table of the task for the appendix using:\n153\tbenchmark.tasks.to_latex()\n154\t```\n155\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ce8031b1-4ff8-4987-8c65-89c1cec47010","uuid":"bd514403-2f53-4662-9158-0d2c06a9aa85","timestamp":"2026-04-13T15:27:52.895Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/README.md","content":"<h1 align=\"center\">\n  <img src=\"https://github.com/embeddings-benchmark/mteb/blob/main/docs/images/logos/mteb_logo/dots-icon.png?raw=true\" alt=\"MTEB\" width=\"28\" style=\"vertical-align: middle; margin-right: 10px;\"/> MTEB\n</h1>\n\n<h3 align=\"center\" style=\"border-bottom: none;\">Multimodal toolbox for evaluating embeddings and retrieval systems</h3>\n\n<p align=\"center\">\n    <a href=\"https://github.com/embeddings-benchmark/mteb/releases\">\n        <img alt=\"GitHub release\" src=\"https://img.shields.io/github/release/embeddings-benchmark/mteb.svg\">\n    </a>\n    <a href=\"https://github.com/embeddings-benchmark/mteb/blob/master/LICENSE\">\n        <img alt=\"License\" src=\"https://img.shields.io/github/license/embeddings-benchmark/mteb.svg?color=green\">\n    </a>\n    <a href=\"https://pepy.tech/project/mteb\">\n        <img alt=\"Downloads\" src=\"https://static.pepy.tech/personalized-badge/mteb?period=total&units=international_system&left_color=grey&right_color=orange&left_text=Downloads\">\n    </a>\n</p>\n\n<h4 align=\"center\">\n    <p>\n        <a href=\"https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/installation/\">Installation</a> |\n        <a href=\"https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/\">Usage</a> |\n        <a href=\"https://huggingface.co/spaces/mteb/leaderboard\">Leaderboard</a> |\n        <a href=\"https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/\">Documentation</a> |\n        <a href=\"#citing\">Citing</a>\n    </p>\n</h4>\n\n\n<h3 align=\"center\">\n    <a href=\"https://huggingface.co/spaces/mteb/leaderboard\"><img style=\"float: middle; padding: 10px 10px 10px 10px;\" width=\"60\" height=\"55\" src=\"https://github.com/embeddings-benchmark/mteb/blob/main/docs/images/logos/hf_logo.png?raw=true\" /></a>\n</h3>\n\n\n## Installation\n\nYou can install mteb simply using pip or uv. For more on installation please see the [documentation](https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/installation/).\n\n```bash\npip install mteb\n```\n\nFor faster installation, you can also use [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/):\n```bash\nuv add mteb\n```\n\n\n## Example Usage\n\nBelow we present a simple use-case example. For more information, see the [documentation](https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/).\n\n```python\nimport mteb\nfrom sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer\n\n# Select model\nmodel_name = \"sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2\"\nmodel = mteb.get_model(model_name) # if the model is not implemented in MTEB it will be eq. to SentenceTransformer(model_name)\n\n# Select tasks\ntasks = mteb.get_tasks(tasks=[\"Banking77Classification.v2\"])\n\n# evaluate\nresults = mteb.evaluate(model, tasks=tasks)\n```\n\nYou can also run it using the CLI:\n\n```bash\nmteb run \\\n    -m sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2 \\\n    -t \"Banking77Classification.v2\" \\\n    --output-folder results\n```\n\nFor more on how to use the CLI check out the [related documentation](https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/get_started/usage/cli/).\n\n## Overview\n\n| Overview                       |                                                                                      |\n|--------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n| 📈 [Leaderboard]               | The interactive leaderboard of the benchmark                                         |\n| **Get Started**.               |                                                                                      |\n| 🏃 [Get Started]               | Overview of how to use mteb                                                          |\n| 🤖 [Defining Models]           | How to use existing model and define custom ones                                     |\n| 📋 [Selecting tasks]           | How to select tasks, benchmarks, splits etc.                                         |\n| 🏭 [Running Evaluation]        | How to run the evaluations, including cache management, speeding up evaluations etc. |\n| 📊 [Loading Results]           | How to load and work with existing model results                                     |\n| **Overview**.                  |                                                                                      |\n| 📋 [Tasks]                     | Overview of available tasks                                                          |\n| 📐 [Benchmarks]                | Overview of available benchmarks                                                     |\n| 🤖 [Models]                    | Overview of available Models                                                         |\n| **Contributing**               |                                                                                      |\n| 🤖 [Adding a model]            | How to submit a model to MTEB and to the leaderboard                                 |\n| 👩‍💻 [Adding a dataset]          | How to add a new task/dataset to MTEB                                                |\n| 👩‍💻 [Adding a benchmark]        | How to add a new benchmark to MTEB and to the leaderboard                            |\n| 🤝 [Contributing]              | How to contribute to MTEB and set it up for development                              |\n\n[Get Started]: https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/\n[Defining Models]: https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/get_started/usage/defining_the_model/\n[Selecting tasks]: https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/get_started/usage/selecting_tasks/\n[Running Evaluation]: https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/get_started/usage/running_the_evaluation/\n[Loading Results]: https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/get_started/usage/loading_results/\n[Tasks]: https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/overview/available_tasks/retrieval/\n[Benchmarks]: https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/overview/available_benchmarks/\n[Models]: https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/overview/available_models/text/\n[Contributing]: https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/CONTRIBUTING/\n[Adding a model]: https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/contributing/adding_a_model/\n[Adding a dataset]: https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/contributing/adding_a_dataset/\n[Adding a benchmark]: https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/contributing/adding_a_benchmark/\n[Leaderboard]: https://huggingface.co/spaces/mteb/leaderboard\n\n## Citing\n\nMTEB was introduced in \"[MTEB: Massive Text Embedding Benchmark](https://arxiv.org/abs/2210.07316)\", and heavily expanded in \"[MMTEB: Massive Multilingual Text Embedding Benchmark](https://arxiv.org/abs/2502.13595)\". When using `mteb`, we recommend that you cite both articles.\n\n<details>\n  <summary> Bibtex Citation (click to unfold) </summary>\n\n\n```bibtex\n@article{muennighoff2022mteb,\n  author = {Muennighoff, Niklas and Tazi, Nouamane and Magne, Loïc and Reimers, Nils},\n  title = {MTEB: Massive Text Embedding Benchmark},\n  publisher = {arXiv},\n  journal={arXiv preprint arXiv:2210.07316},\n  year = {2022},\n  url = {https://arxiv.org/abs/2210.07316},\n  doi = {10.48550/ARXIV.2210.07316},\n}\n\n@article{enevoldsen2025mmtebmassivemultilingualtext,\n  title={MMTEB: Massive Multilingual Text Embedding Benchmark},\n  author={Kenneth Enevoldsen and Isaac Chung and Imene Kerboua and Márton Kardos and Ashwin Mathur and David Stap and Jay Gala and Wissam Siblini and Dominik Krzemiński and Genta Indra Winata and Saba Sturua and Saiteja Utpala and Mathieu Ciancone and Marion Schaeffer and Gabriel Sequeira and Diganta Misra and Shreeya Dhakal and Jonathan Rystrøm and Roman Solomatin and Ömer Çağatan and Akash Kundu and Martin Bernstorff and Shitao Xiao and Akshita Sukhlecha and Bhavish Pahwa and Rafał Poświata and Kranthi Kiran GV and Shawon Ashraf and Daniel Auras and Björn Plüster and Jan Philipp Harries and Loïc Magne and Isabelle Mohr and Mariya Hendriksen and Dawei Zhu and Hippolyte Gisserot-Boukhlef and Tom Aarsen and Jan Kostkan and Konrad Wojtasik and Taemin Lee and Marek Šuppa and Crystina Zhang and Roberta Rocca and Mohammed Hamdy and Andrianos Michail and John Yang and Manuel Faysse and Aleksei Vatolin and Nandan Thakur and Manan Dey and Dipam Vasani and Pranjal Chitale and Simone Tedeschi and Nguyen Tai and Artem Snegirev and Michael Günther and Mengzhou Xia and Weijia Shi and Xing Han Lù and Jordan Clive and Gayatri Krishnakumar and Anna Maksimova and Silvan Wehrli and Maria Tikhonova and Henil Panchal and Aleksandr Abramov and Malte Ostendorff and Zheng Liu and Simon Clematide and Lester James Miranda and Alena Fenogenova and Guangyu Song and Ruqiya Bin Safi and Wen-Ding Li and Alessia Borghini and Federico Cassano and Hongjin Su and Jimmy Lin and Howard Yen and Lasse Hansen and Sara Hooker and Chenghao Xiao and Vaibhav Adlakha and Orion Weller and Siva Reddy and Niklas Muennighoff},\n  publisher = {arXiv},\n  journal={arXiv preprint arXiv:2502.13595},\n  year={2025},\n  url={https://arxiv.org/abs/2502.13595},\n  doi = {10.48550/arXiv.2502.13595},\n}\n```\n</details>\n\n\nIf you use any of the specific benchmarks, we also recommend that you cite the authors of both the benchmark and its tasks:\n\n```py\nbenchmark = mteb.get_benchmark(\"MTEB(eng, v2)\")\nbenchmark.citation # get citation for a specific benchmark\n\n# you can also create a table of the task for the appendix using:\nbenchmark.tasks.to_latex()\n```\n","numLines":155,"startLine":1,"totalLines":155}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0cc05aba411c466094fc1d55","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t[build-system]\n2\trequires = [\"setuptools>=42\", \"wheel\"]\n3\tbuild-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n4\t\n5\t[project]\n6\tname = \"mteb\"\n7\tversion = \"2.12.16\"\n8\tdescription = \"Massive Text Embedding Benchmark\"\n9\treadme = \"README.md\"\n10\tauthors = [\n11\t    { name = \"MTEB Contributors\", email = \"niklas@huggingface.co\" },\n12\t    { name = \"Kenneth Enevoldsen\", email = \"kenneth.enevoldsen@cas.au.dk\" },\n13\t    { name = \"Nouamane Tazi\", email = \"nouamane@huggingface.co\" },\n14\t    { name = \"Nils Reimers\", email = \"info@nils-reimers.de\" },\n15\t]\n16\tmaintainers = [\n17\t    { name = \"Kenneth Enevoldsen\", email = \"kenneth.enevoldsen@cas.au.dk\" },\n18\t    { name = \"Roman Solomatin\", email = \"risolomatin@gmail.com\" },\n19\t    { name = \"Isaac Chung\", email = \"chungisaac1217@gmail.com\" },\n20\t]\n21\tlicense = \"Apache-2.0\"\n22\tlicense-files = [\"LICENSE\"]\n23\tkeywords = [\"deep learning\", \"text embeddings\", \"embeddings\", \"multimodal\", \"benchmark\", \"retrieval\", \"information retrieval\"]\n24\tclassifiers = [\n25\t    \"Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable\",\n26\t    \"Environment :: Console\",\n27\t    \"Intended Audience :: Developers\",\n28\t    \"Intended Audience :: Information Technology\",\n29\t    \"Operating System :: OS Independent\",\n30\t    \"Programming Language :: Python\",\n31\t]\n32\trequires-python = \">=3.10,<3.15\"\n33\tdependencies = [\n34\t    \"datasets>=2.19.0\",\n35\t    \"numpy>=1.23.0,<3.0.0\",\n36\t    \"requests>=2.26.0\",\n37\t    \"scikit-learn>=1.4.0\",\n38\t    \"scipy>=1.14.0\",\n39\t    \"sentence_transformers>=3.0.0\",\n40\t    \"transformers>=4.40.0,<6.0.0\",\n41\t    \"typing-extensions>=4.5.0\",\n42\t    \"torch>=2.0.0\",\n43\t    \"tqdm>1.0.0\",\n44\t    \"rich>=13.0.0\",\n45\t    \"pytrec-eval-terrier>=0.5.6\",\n46\t    \"pydantic>=2.11.0\",\n47\t    \"polars>=1.0.0\",\n48\t]\n49\t\n50\t\n51\t[project.urls]\n52\tHomepage = \"https://github.com/embeddings-benchmark/mteb\"\n53\tDocumentation = \"https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/\"\n54\tRepository = \"https://github.com/embeddings-benchmark/mteb\"\n55\t\"Hugging Face Organization\" = \"https://huggingface.co/mteb\"\n56\t\n57\t[project.scripts]\n58\tmteb = \"mteb.cli:main\"\n59\t\n60\t[project.optional-dependencies]\n61\timage = [\n62\t    \"torchvision>0.2.1\",\n63\t    \"transformers[torch-vision,vision]\",\n64\t]\n65\taudio = [\n66\t    \"torchaudio\",\n67\t    # datsaets==4 requires transformers>=5, because of https://github.com/huggingface/transformers/issues/42103\n68\t    \"datasets[audio]\",\n69\t]\n70\tcodecarbon = [\"codecarbon>=2.0.0,<3.0.0\"]\n71\tleaderboard = [\n72\t    \"gradio==6.0.1\",\n73\t    \"plotly>=5.24.0,<6.0.0\",\n74\t    \"cachetools>=5.2.0\",\n75\t    \"matplotlib>=3.9.4\",\n76\t    \"pymongo>=4.15.5\",\n77\t]\n78\tvideo = [\"torchcodec\"]\n79\t\n80\t# model specific optional dependencies:\n81\tpeft = [\"peft>=0.11.0\"]\n82\tflagembedding = [\"FlagEmbedding==1.3.4\"]\n83\tjina = [\"einops>=0.8.0\"]\n84\tjina-clip = [\"peft>=0.15.2\", \"einops>=0.8.0\", \"transformers>=4.52.0,<5.0.0\", \"torchvision>=0.22.1\", \"timm>=1.0.15,<1.1.0\"]\n85\tjina-v4 = [\"peft>=0.15.2\", \"transformers>=4.52.0,<5.0.0\", \"torchvision>=0.22.1\"]\n86\tflash_attention = [\"flash-attn>=2.6.3\"]\n87\topenai = [\"openai>=1.41.0\", \"tiktoken>=0.8.0\"]\n88\tmodel2vec = [\"model2vec>=0.3.0\"]\n89\tpylate = [\"pylate>=1.3.1; python_full_version < '3.13'\", \"transformers>=4.52.0; python_full_version < '3.13'\"]  # Required for sentence-transformers 5.0.0 compatibility (otherwise 1.1.6), pylate requires voyager, which in turn requires <=3.12\n90\tmsclap = [\"msclap>=1.3.4\", \"soundfile>=0.13.1\"]\n91\tbm25s = [\"bm25s>=0.2.6\", \"PyStemmer>=2.2.0.3\"]\n92\tgritlm = [\"gritlm>=1.0.2\"]\n93\txformers = [\"xformers>=0.0.29\"]\n94\tblip2 = [\"salesforce-lavis>=1.0.2\"]\n95\tvoyageai = [\"voyageai>0.3.0,<2.0.0\"]\n96\tvoyage_v = [\"voyageai>0.3.0,<2.0.0\", \"tenacity>9.0.0\"]\n97\tcohere = [\"cohere==5.14.0\"]\n98\tvertexai = [\"vertexai==1.71.1\"]\n99\tllm2vec = [\"llm2vec>=0.2.3,<0.3.0\"]\n100\ttimm = [\"timm>=1.0.15,<1.1.0\"]\n101\topen_clip_torch = [\"open_clip_torch==2.31.0\"]\n102\tnomic = [\"einops>=0.8.1\"]\n103\tark = [\"volcengine-python-sdk[ark]==3.0.2\", \"tiktoken>=0.8.0\"]\n104\tcolpali_engine = [\"colpali_engine>=0.3.12; python_full_version < '3.14'\"]\n105\tcolqwen3 = [\"transformers>=4.57.0\", \"torchvision>=0.22.1\"]\n106\tsauerkrautlm-colpali = [\"sauerkrautlm-colpali>=0.1.0; python_full_version < '3.14'\"]\n107\txet = [\"huggingface_hub>=0.32.0\"]\n108\tyoutu = [\"tencentcloud-sdk-python-common>=3.0.1454\", \"tencentcloud-sdk-python-lkeap>=3.0.1451\"]\n109\tllama-embed-nemotron = [\"transformers==4.51.0\"]\n110\tllama-nemotron-colembed-vl = [\"transformers[torch]==4.49.0\", \"torchvision>=0.22.0\", \"flash-attn>=2.6.3\", \"accelerate\"]\n111\tnemotron-colembed-vl-v2 = [\"transformers[torch]==5.0.0\", \"torchvision>=0.22.0\", \"flash-attn>=2.6.3\", \"accelerate\"]\n112\tllama-nemotron-embed-vl-1b-v2 = [\"transformers[torch]>=4.56.0\", \"torchvision>=0.22.0\", \"flash-attn>=2.6.3\", \"accelerate\"]\n113\tfaiss-cpu = [\"faiss-cpu>=1.12.0\"]\n114\teager_embed = [\"qwen_vl_utils>=0.0.14\"]\n115\tspeechbrain = [\"speechbrain>=0.5.12\"]\n116\tmuq = [\"muq==0.1.0\"]\n117\twav2clip = [\"wav2clip==0.1.0\"]\n118\ttorch-vggish-yamnet = [\"torch-vggish-yamnet==0.2.1\"]\n119\tvllm = [\"vllm>=0.11.1\"]\n120\tmctct = [\"transformers<5\"]  # mctct was removed in transformers 5\n121\tsiglip = [\"sentencepiece>=0.2.0\",\"protobuf>=3.0.0\"]\n122\tqwen-vl = [\"transformers>=4.57.0\", \"qwen-vl-utils>=0.0.14\"]\n123\t\n124\t[dependency-groups]\n125\tlint = [\n126\t    \"ruff==0.14.0\", # locked so we don't get PRs which fail only due to a lint update\n127\t    \"pre-commit>=4.1.0\",\n128\t    \"typos>1\",\n129\t    \"bibtexparser>=1.4.3\", # used for tests/test_citation_formatting.py\n130\t]\n131\ttest = [\n132\t    \"pytest>=8.3.4,<8.4.0\",\n133\t    \"pytest-xdist>=3.6.1,<3.7.0\",\n134\t    \"pytest-coverage>=0.0\",\n135\t    \"pytest-rerunfailures>=15.0,<16.0\",\n136\t    \"iso639>=0.1.4\", # used for tests/scripts/test_generate_model_meta.py\n137\t    \"GitPython>=3.0.0\",\n138\t    \"tabulate>=0.9.0\",\n139\t    \"bibtexparser>=1.4.3\", # used for tests/test_citation_formatting.py\n140\t]\n141\tdocs = [\n142\t    \"zensical>=0.0.11\",\n143\t    \"mkdocstrings-python>=1.18.2\",\n144\t    \"tabulate>=0.9.0\",\n145\t]\n146\ttyping = [\n147\t    \"mypy==1.19.1\",\n148\t    \"types-cachetools>=6.2.0.20250827\",\n149\t    \"types-pysocks>=1.7.1.20250828\",\n150\t    \"types-pyyaml>=6.0.12.20250822\",\n151\t    \"types-requests>=2.32.4.20250913\",\n152\t    \"types-simplejson>=3.20.0.20250822\",\n153\t    \"types-tqdm>=4.67.0.20250809\",\n154\t    \"types-tensorflow>=2.18.0.20250809\",\n155\t    \"types-pygments>=2.19.0.20251121\",\n156\t    \"types-colorama>=0.4.15.20250801\",\n157\t    \"types-gevent>=25.9.0.20251102\",\n158\t    \"types-networkx>=3.6.1.20251220\",\n159\t    \"types-openpyxl>=3.1.5.20250919\",\n160\t    \"types-psutil>=7.1.3.20251211\",\n161\t    \"types-python-dateutil>=2.9.0.20251115\",\n162\t    \"types-pywin32>=311.0.0.20251008\",\n163\t    \"types-regex>=2025.11.3.20251106\",\n164\t    \"types-setuptools>=80.9.0.20251221\",\n165\t    \"types-tabulate>=0.9.0.20241207\",\n166\t    \"types-xlrd>=2.0.0.20251020\",\n167\t    \"pandas-stubs>=2.3.2.250926\",\n168\t    \"scipy-stubs>=1.15.3.0\",\n169\t    \"types-defusedxml>=0.7.0.20250822\",\n170\t    \"pillow>=12.0.0\",\n171\t]\n172\tdev = [\n173\t    {include-group = \"lint\"},\n174\t    {include-group = \"test\"},\n175\t    {include-group = \"typing\"},\n176\t    {include-group = \"docs\"},\n177\t]\n178\t\n179\t\n180\t[tool.coverage.report]\n181\tomit = [\"tests/*\", \"mteb/tasks/**/*\", \"scripts\"]\n182\t\n183\t# Regexes for lines to exclude from consideration\n184\texclude_also = [\n185\t    # Don't complain about missing debug-only code:\n186\t    \"def __repr__\",\n187\t    \"if self\\\\.debug\",\n188\t\n189\t    # Don't complain if tests don't hit defensive assertion code:\n190\t    \"raise AssertionError\",\n191\t    \"raise NotImplementedError\",\n192\t\n193\t    # Don't complain if non-runnable code isn't run:\n194\t    \"if 0:\",\n195\t    \"if __name__ == .__main__.:\",\n196\t\n197\t    # Don't complain about abstract methods, they aren't run:\n198\t    \"@(abc\\\\.)?abstractmethod\",\n199\t]\n200\t\n201\t[tool.setuptools.packages.find]\n202\twhere = [\".\"]\n203\tinclude = [\"mteb\", \"mteb.*\"]\n204\tnamespaces = false\n205\t\n206\t[tool.setuptools.package-data]\n207\t\"mteb\" = [\n208\t    \"languages/*.json\",  # for languages\n209\t    \"descriptive_stats/*/*.json\",  # for descriptive_stats image\n210\t    \"descriptive_stats/Image/*/*.json\",  # for descriptive_stats image\n211\t]\n212\t\"mteb.abstasks\" = [\"dataset_card_template.md\"]\n213\t\"mteb.tasks.zeroshot_classification.eng.templates\" = [\"*.txt\"]\n214\t\n215\t[tool.ruff]\n216\ttarget-version = \"py310\"\n217\t\n218\t\n219\t[tool.ruff.lint]\n220\tselect = [\n221\t    \"F\",  # pyflakes rules,\n222\t    \"I\",  # sorting for imports\n223\t    \"E\",  # formatting for docs\n224\t    \"D\",  # formatting for docs\n225\t    \"UP\", # upgrade to latest syntax if possible\n226\t    \"FA\", # Future annotations\n227\t    \"C4\", # cleaner comprehensions\n228\t    \"NPY\", # numpy\n229\t    \"N\",       # PEP8 naming convention\n230\t    \"RUF009\",  # function-call-in-dataclass-default-argument\n231\t    \"RUF008\",  # mutable-dataclass-default\n232\t    \"RUF013\",  # implicit-optional\n233\t    \"RUF012\",  # mutable-class-default\n234\t    \"RUF015\",  # unnecessary-iterable-allocation-for-first-element\n235\t    \"RUF016\",  # invalid-index-type\n236\t    \"RUF017\",  # quadratic-list-summation\n237\t    \"RUF018\",  # assignment-in-assert\n238\t    \"RUF019\",  # unnecessary-key-check\n239\t    \"RUF020\",  # never-union\n240\t    \"RUF021\",  # parenthesize-chained-operators\n241\t    \"RUF022\",  # unsorted-dunder-all\n242\t    \"RUF024\",  # mutable-fromkeys-value\n243\t    \"RUF026\",  # default-factory-kwarg\n244\t    \"RUF033\",  # post-init-default\n245\t    \"RUF034\",  # useless-if-else\n246\t    \"RUF041\",  # unnecessary-nested-literal\n247\t    \"RUF040\",  # invalid-assert-message-literal-argument\n248\t    \"RUF046\",  # unnecessary-cast-to-int\n249\t    \"RUF051\",  # if-key-in-dict-del\n250\t    \"RUF100\",  # unused-noqa\n251\t    \"RUF101\",  # redirected-noqa\n252\t    \"RUF200\",  # invalid-pyproject-toml\n253\t    \"PTH\",     # use pathlib\n254\t    \"TID\",     # tidy-imports\n255\t    \"D\",       # pydocstyle\n256\t    \"PGH\",     # pygrep-hooks Use specific rule codes when ignoring type issues\n257\t    \"LOG\",     # logging\n258\t    \"TC\",      # type-checking\n259\t    \"T20\",     # don't allow print\n260\t    \"PL\",      # pylint\n261\t    \"S\",       # flake8-bandit\n262\t]\n263\t\n264\tignore = [\n265\t    \"E501\",   # line too long\n266\t    \"E741\",     # ambiguous variable name\n267\t    \"D100\",     # Missing docstring in public module\n268\t    \"D105\",     # Missing docstring in magic method\n269\t    \"D104\",     # Missing docstring in public package\n270\t    \"D107\",     # Missing docstring in __init__\n271\t    \"D415\",     # First line should end with a period\n272\t    \"C408\",     # don't use unecc. collection call, e.g. dict over {}\n273\t    \"S404\",    # subprocess import insecure\n274\t    \"S311\",     # standard pseudo-random generators are fine for non-crypto use\n275\t    \"S104\",     # allow binding to all interfaces in tests\n276\t    \"S607\",     # start a process with partial path\n277\t    \"S603\",   # allow subprocess calls with shell=True\n278\t    \"PLR2004\",   # magic value comparison\n279\t    \"PLC0415\",   # import outside of top-level\n280\t    \"PLR0912\",  # too many branches\n281\t    \"PLR0915\",  # too many statements\n282\t]\n283\tfuture-annotations = true  # For TC rules\n284\ttyping-modules = [\"typing_extensions\", \"mteb.types\", \"collections.abc\"]\n285\tpreview = true\n286\t\n287\t\n288\t[tool.ruff.lint.per-file-ignores]\n289\t\"scripts/*\" = [\"ALL\"]\n290\t\"docs/*\" = [\n291\t    \"D\",\n292\t    \"DOC\",\n293\t    \"S101\"\n294\t]\n295\t\"tests/*\" = [\n296\t    \"RUF012\",\n297\t    \"D\",\n298\t    \"DOC\",\n299\t    \"TC\",\n300\t    \"S101\",  # allow asserts in tests\n301\t    \"S602\",  # allow shell=True in tests\n302\t    \"S603\",  # allow subprocess calls in tests\n303\t]\n304\t\"mteb/tasks/*__init__.py\" = [\"F403\"]  # undefined import `from .lang import *`\n305\t\"mteb/tasks/*\" = [\n306\t    \"D\",\n307\t    \"DOC\",\n308\t]\n309\t\"mteb/models/model_implementations/*\" = [\n310\t    \"D\",\n311\t    \"DOC\",\n312\t]\n313\t\"mteb/benchmarks/benchmark.py\" = [\n314\t    # pydantic would try to validate fields in Benchmark class\n315\t    \"TC\",\n316\t]\n317\t\"mteb/leaderboard/app.py\" = [\n318\t    # gradio would try to validate typehints\n319\t    \"TC002\",\n320\t    \"TC001\",\n321\t]\n322\t\n323\t\n324\t[tool.ruff.lint.flake8-implicit-str-concat]\n325\tallow-multiline = false\n326\t\n327\t[tool.ruff.lint.pep8-naming]\n328\tignore-names = [\n329\t    \"F\",  # torch.nn.functional\n330\t    \"X\",\n331\t    \"X_train\",\n332\t    \"X_test\",\n333\t]\n334\t\n335\t[tool.ruff.lint.pydocstyle]\n336\tconvention = \"google\"\n337\t\n338\t[tool.ruff.lint.flake8-annotations]\n339\tmypy-init-return = true\n340\tsuppress-none-returning = true\n341\t\n342\t[tool.ruff.lint.flake8-type-checking]\n343\tstrict = true\n344\truntime-evaluated-base-classes = [\n345\t    \"pydantic.BaseModel\",\n346\t    \"mteb.abstasks.task_metadata.TaskMetadata\",  # https://github.com/astral-sh/ruff/issues/7866\n347\t]\n348\t\n349\t[tool.ruff.lint.pylint]\n350\tmax-args = 9\n351\t\n352\t[tool.semantic_release]\n353\tbranch = \"main\"\n354\tversion_toml = [\"pyproject.toml:project.version\"]\n355\tbuild_command = \"python -m pip install build; python -m build\"\n356\ttag_format = \"{version}\"\n357\t\n358\t[tool.semantic_release.commit_parser_options]\n359\tminor_tags = [\"minor\", \"feat\", \"benchmark\"]\n360\tpatch_tags = [\n361\t    \"patch\",\n362\t    \"fix\",\n363\t    \"perf\",\n364\t    \"model\",\n365\t    \"dataset\",\n366\t]\n367\t\n368\t[tool.pytest.ini_options]\n369\taddopts = \"\"\"\n370\t    -ra\n371\t    --reruns 3\n372\t    --only-rerun requests.exceptions.ReadTimeout\n373\t    --only-rerun huggingface_hub.errors.HfHubHTTPError\n374\t    --only-rerun huggingface_hub.errors.LocalEntryNotFoundError\n375\t    --only-rerun FileNotFoundError\n376\t    --durations=5\n377\t    --reruns-delay 10\n378\t\"\"\"\n379\t# -ra -> # show extra test summary info for skipped, failed, etc.\n380\t# --reruns 3 -> # Retry failed tests 3 times\n381\t# requests.exceptions.ReadTimeout -> # HF Read timed out -> https://github.com/embeddings-benchmark/mteb/actions/runs/13275350693/job/37093688544\n382\t# huggingface_hub.errors.HfHubHTTPError -> # HF is unavailable, e.g. seen here: https://github.com/embeddings-benchmark/mteb/actions/runs/13275350693/job/37093688544\n383\t# huggingface_hub.errors.LocalEntryNotFoundError -> # Gateway Time-out from HF, e.g. seen here: https://github.com/embeddings-benchmark/mteb/actions/runs/13275350693/job/37093688544\n384\t# FileNotFoundError -> HF Cache is broken:  https://github.com/embeddings-benchmark/mteb/actions/runs/13302915091/job/37147507251?pr=2029\n385\t# --durations=5 -> Show the 5 slowest tests\n386\t# --reruns-delay 10 -> Delay between reruns in seconds to avoid running into the same issue again\n387\t\n388\tmarkers = [\n389\t    \"test_datasets: marks tests that tests dataset availability\",\n390\t]\n391\t\n392\t[tool.uv]\n393\tdefault-groups = [\"test\", \"docs\", \"typing\", \"lint\"]\n394\toverride-dependencies = [\n395\t    \"salesforce-lavis\", # salesforce-lavis is not valid with sentence transformers >=3.0.0\n396\t]\n397\tconflicts = [\n398\t    [\n399\t        { extra = \"timm\" },\n400\t        { extra = \"blip2\" },\n401\t        { extra = \"llm2vec\" },\n402\t        { extra = \"model2vec\" },\n403\t        { extra = \"pylate\" }, # conflicting versions of transformers\n404\t        { extra = \"llama-embed-nemotron\" }, # conflicting versions of transformers\n405\t        { extra = \"llama-nemotron-colembed-vl\" }, # conflicting versions of transformers\n406\t        { extra = \"nemotron-colembed-vl-v2\" }, # conflicting versions of transformers\n407\t        { extra = \"llama-nemotron-embed-vl-1b-v2\" }, # conflicting versions of transformers\n408\t        { extra = \"colpali_engine\" },\n409\t        { extra = \"colqwen3\" },\n410\t        { extra = \"jina-v4\" },\n411\t        { extra = \"sauerkrautlm-colpali\" },\n412\t        { extra = \"vllm\" },\n413\t        { extra = \"jina-clip\" },\n414\t        { extra = \"msclap\" },\n415\t        { extra = \"muq\" },\n416\t        { extra = \"mctct\" },\n417\t        { extra = \"qwen-vl\" },\n418\t    ],\n419\t]\n420\t\n421\t[tool.uv.extra-build-dependencies]\n422\tflash-attn = [{ requirement = \"torch\", match-runtime = true }]\n423\t\n424\t[tool.mypy]\n425\tplugins = ['pydantic.mypy']\n426\t\n427\t[[tool.mypy.overrides]]\n428\t# these modules not typed and don't have stubs\n429\tmodule = [\n430\t    \"datasets\",\n431\t    \"datasets.exceptions\",\n432\t    \"sklearn\",\n433\t    \"sklearn.*\",\n434\t    \"faiss\",\n435\t    \"vllm\",\n436\t    \"torchaudio\",\n437\t    \"torchcodec\",\n438\t]\n439\tignore_missing_imports = true\n440\t\n441\t[[tool.mypy.overrides]]\n442\t# don't typecheck these modules (too many issues)\n443\tmodule = [\n444\t    \"mteb.models.model_implementations.*\",\n445\t    \"mteb.tasks.*\",\n446\t    \"mteb.leaderboard.*\",\n447\t]\n448\tignore_errors = true\n449\t\n450\t[[tool.mypy.overrides]]\n451\t# mypy can't resolve dataset dict\n452\tmodule = [\"mteb.abstasks.*\"]\n453\tdisable_error_code = [\"index\"]\n454\t\n455\t[tool.typos.default]\n456\tbinary = false\n457\tlocale = \"en\"\n458\textend-ignore-words-re = [\n459\t    \"Classfication\", # misspelled task name\n460\t    \"nd\", # license\n461\t    # authors\n462\t    \"Stap\",\n463\t    \"Asai\",\n464\t    \"Tung\",\n465\t    \"Gool\",\n466\t    \"Winn\",\n467\t    \"STIL\",\n468\t    \"Sherif\",\n469\t    \"Mor\",\n470\t    \"Ond\",\n471\t    \"Mehta\",\n472\t    \"Parth\",\n473\t    # languages/bibtext artifacts\n474\t    \"SHW\",\n475\t    \"ba\",\n476\t    \"creen\",\n477\t    \"Accademia\",\n478\t    \"dementieva\",\n479\t    \"Expresso\",\n480\t    \"expresso\",\n481\t    \"Iz\",\n482\t    \"Allo\",\n483\t    \"Soler\",\n484\t    # language keys:\n485\t    \"tha\",\n486\t    \"yor\",\n487\t    \"als\",\n488\t    \"bre\",\n489\t    \"thi\",\n490\t    # ISO 15924 script codes\n491\t    \"Beng\",  # Bengali script\n492\t\n493\t]\n494\textend-ignore-re = [\n495\t    \"author.*\",  # ignore authors in citations\n496\t    \"editor.*\",  # ignore authors in citations\n497\t]\n498\t\n499\t[tool.typos.files]\n500\textend-exclude = [\n501\t    \"*.json\",\n502\t    \"*.jsonl\",\n503\t    \"*.cff\",\n504\t    \"*.tex\",  # latex files with language codes\n505\t    \"*.bib\",  # bibliography files with author names and journal abbreviations\n506\t    \"*.txt\",  # zero shot labels\n507\t    \"docs/mmteb\",\n508\t    \"scripts/\",\n509\t    \"mteb/models/model_implementations/gme_v_models.py\",  # video_grid_thw `thw`\n510\t    \"mteb/models/model_implementations/vista_models.py\",  # self.normlized: in visual bge\n511\t    \"mteb/models/model_implementations/salesforce_models.py\", # multiligual in paper title\n512\t    \"tests/mock_tasks.py\",  #  \"denne her matche ikke den ovenstående\",\n513\t    \"mteb/models/model_implementations/kalm_models.py\",  # prompt:  classify ist topic\",\n514\t    \"mteb/tasks/reranking/eng/built_bench_reranking.py\",  # prompt:   descriptions from buit asset\n515\t    \"mteb/tasks/retrieval/eng/built_bench_retrieval.py\",\n516\t    \"mteb/tasks/retrieval/eng/llava_it2t_retrieval.py\",\n517\t    # dutch prompts\n518\t    \"mteb/tasks/classification/nld/\",\n519\t    \"mteb/tasks/clustering/nld/\",\n520\t    \"mteb/tasks/multilabel_classification/nld/\",\n521\t    \"mteb/tasks/pair_classification/nld/\",\n522\t    \"mteb/tasks/sts/nld/\",\n523\t    \"mteb/tasks/retrieval/nld/\",\n524\t    \"mteb/descriptive_stats/\",\n525\t    # Beltagy, Iz\n526\t    \"mteb/tasks/retrieval/eng/lembqm_sum_retrieval.py\",\n527\t    \"mteb/tasks/classification/jpn/wrime_classification.py\",\n528\t    \"mteb/tasks/reranking/eng/sci_docs_reranking.py\",\n529\t]\n530\t\n531\t[tool.typos.type.py]\n532\textend-ignore-re = [\n533\t    # ignore lang identifiers\n534\t    \"...-....\",\n535\t    \"..._....\",\n536\t]\n537\t\n538\t[tool.typos.type.py.extend-identifiers]\n539\tBulgarianStoreReviewSentimentClassfication = \"BulgarianStoreReviewSentimentClassfication\"\n540\t\n541\t[tool.typos.type.py.extend-words]\n542\twdth = \"wdth\"\n543\tAllo = \"Allo\"\n544\tsom = \"som\"\n545\tyor = \"yor\"\n546\tBeng = \"Beng\"\n547\tals = \"als\"\n548\ttha = \"tha\"\n549\ttham = \"tham\"\n550\tthi = \"thi\"\n551\tbre = \"bre\"\n552\tmak = \"mak\"\n553\tMaka = \"Maka\"\n554\tMape = \"Mape\"\n555\tMian = \"Mian\"\n556\tOno = \"Ono\"\n557\tYau = \"Yau\"\n558\tAltas = \"Altas\"\n559\tmatche = \"matche\"\n560\texpresso = \"expresso\"\n561\tExpresso = \"Expresso\"\n562\tNIFE = \"NIFE\"\n563\tthw = \"thw\"\n564\tist = \"ist\" # spelling error in prompt for harrier-oss-v1\n565\tshw = \"SHW\"\n566\tnd = \"nd\"\n567\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ce8031b1-4ff8-4987-8c65-89c1cec47010","uuid":"fba31e40-cd48-4e54-aa64-ea30ee68f5f4","timestamp":"2026-04-13T15:27:52.898Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/pyproject.toml","content":"[build-system]\nrequires = [\"setuptools>=42\", \"wheel\"]\nbuild-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n\n[project]\nname = \"mteb\"\nversion = \"2.12.16\"\ndescription = \"Massive Text Embedding Benchmark\"\nreadme = \"README.md\"\nauthors = [\n    { name = \"MTEB Contributors\", email = \"niklas@huggingface.co\" },\n    { name = \"Kenneth Enevoldsen\", email = \"kenneth.enevoldsen@cas.au.dk\" },\n    { name = \"Nouamane Tazi\", email = \"nouamane@huggingface.co\" },\n    { name = \"Nils Reimers\", email = \"info@nils-reimers.de\" },\n]\nmaintainers = [\n    { name = \"Kenneth Enevoldsen\", email = \"kenneth.enevoldsen@cas.au.dk\" },\n    { name = \"Roman Solomatin\", email = \"risolomatin@gmail.com\" },\n    { name = \"Isaac Chung\", email = \"chungisaac1217@gmail.com\" },\n]\nlicense = \"Apache-2.0\"\nlicense-files = [\"LICENSE\"]\nkeywords = [\"deep learning\", \"text embeddings\", \"embeddings\", \"multimodal\", \"benchmark\", \"retrieval\", \"information retrieval\"]\nclassifiers = [\n    \"Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable\",\n    \"Environment :: Console\",\n    \"Intended Audience :: Developers\",\n    \"Intended Audience :: Information Technology\",\n    \"Operating System :: OS Independent\",\n    \"Programming Language :: Python\",\n]\nrequires-python = \">=3.10,<3.15\"\ndependencies = [\n    \"datasets>=2.19.0\",\n    \"numpy>=1.23.0,<3.0.0\",\n    \"requests>=2.26.0\",\n    \"scikit-learn>=1.4.0\",\n    \"scipy>=1.14.0\",\n    \"sentence_transformers>=3.0.0\",\n    \"transformers>=4.40.0,<6.0.0\",\n    \"typing-extensions>=4.5.0\",\n    \"torch>=2.0.0\",\n    \"tqdm>1.0.0\",\n    \"rich>=13.0.0\",\n    \"pytrec-eval-terrier>=0.5.6\",\n    \"pydantic>=2.11.0\",\n    \"polars>=1.0.0\",\n]\n\n\n[project.urls]\nHomepage = \"https://github.com/embeddings-benchmark/mteb\"\nDocumentation = \"https://embeddings-benchmark.github.io/mteb/\"\nRepository = \"https://github.com/embeddings-benchmark/mteb\"\n\"Hugging Face Organization\" = \"https://huggingface.co/mteb\"\n\n[project.scripts]\nmteb = \"mteb.cli:main\"\n\n[project.optional-dependencies]\nimage = [\n    \"torchvision>0.2.1\",\n    \"transformers[torch-vision,vision]\",\n]\naudio = [\n    \"torchaudio\",\n    # datsaets==4 requires transformers>=5, because of https://github.com/huggingface/transformers/issues/42103\n    \"datasets[audio]\",\n]\ncodecarbon = [\"codecarbon>=2.0.0,<3.0.0\"]\nleaderboard = [\n    \"gradio==6.0.1\",\n    \"plotly>=5.24.0,<6.0.0\",\n    \"cachetools>=5.2.0\",\n    \"matplotlib>=3.9.4\",\n    \"pymongo>=4.15.5\",\n]\nvideo = [\"torchcodec\"]\n\n# model specific optional dependencies:\npeft = [\"peft>=0.11.0\"]\nflagembedding = [\"FlagEmbedding==1.3.4\"]\njina = [\"einops>=0.8.0\"]\njina-clip = [\"peft>=0.15.2\", \"einops>=0.8.0\", \"transformers>=4.52.0,<5.0.0\", \"torchvision>=0.22.1\", \"timm>=1.0.15,<1.1.0\"]\njina-v4 = [\"peft>=0.15.2\", \"transformers>=4.52.0,<5.0.0\", \"torchvision>=0.22.1\"]\nflash_attention = [\"flash-attn>=2.6.3\"]\nopenai = [\"openai>=1.41.0\", \"tiktoken>=0.8.0\"]\nmodel2vec = [\"model2vec>=0.3.0\"]\npylate = [\"pylate>=1.3.1; python_full_version < '3.13'\", \"transformers>=4.52.0; python_full_version < '3.13'\"]  # Required for sentence-transformers 5.0.0 compatibility (otherwise 1.1.6), pylate requires voyager, which in turn requires <=3.12\nmsclap = [\"msclap>=1.3.4\", \"soundfile>=0.13.1\"]\nbm25s = [\"bm25s>=0.2.6\", \"PyStemmer>=2.2.0.3\"]\ngritlm = [\"gritlm>=1.0.2\"]\nxformers = [\"xformers>=0.0.29\"]\nblip2 = [\"salesforce-lavis>=1.0.2\"]\nvoyageai = [\"voyageai>0.3.0,<2.0.0\"]\nvoyage_v = [\"voyageai>0.3.0,<2.0.0\", \"tenacity>9.0.0\"]\ncohere = [\"cohere==5.14.0\"]\nvertexai = [\"vertexai==1.71.1\"]\nllm2vec = [\"llm2vec>=0.2.3,<0.3.0\"]\ntimm = [\"timm>=1.0.15,<1.1.0\"]\nopen_clip_torch = [\"open_clip_torch==2.31.0\"]\nnomic = [\"einops>=0.8.1\"]\nark = [\"volcengine-python-sdk[ark]==3.0.2\", \"tiktoken>=0.8.0\"]\ncolpali_engine = [\"colpali_engine>=0.3.12; python_full_version < '3.14'\"]\ncolqwen3 = [\"transformers>=4.57.0\", \"torchvision>=0.22.1\"]\nsauerkrautlm-colpali = [\"sauerkrautlm-colpali>=0.1.0; python_full_version < '3.14'\"]\nxet = [\"huggingface_hub>=0.32.0\"]\nyoutu = [\"tencentcloud-sdk-python-common>=3.0.1454\", \"tencentcloud-sdk-python-lkeap>=3.0.1451\"]\nllama-embed-nemotron = [\"transformers==4.51.0\"]\nllama-nemotron-colembed-vl = [\"transformers[torch]==4.49.0\", \"torchvision>=0.22.0\", \"flash-attn>=2.6.3\", \"accelerate\"]\nnemotron-colembed-vl-v2 = [\"transformers[torch]==5.0.0\", \"torchvision>=0.22.0\", \"flash-attn>=2.6.3\", \"accelerate\"]\nllama-nemotron-embed-vl-1b-v2 = [\"transformers[torch]>=4.56.0\", \"torchvision>=0.22.0\", \"flash-attn>=2.6.3\", \"accelerate\"]\nfaiss-cpu = [\"faiss-cpu>=1.12.0\"]\neager_embed = [\"qwen_vl_utils>=0.0.14\"]\nspeechbrain = [\"speechbrain>=0.5.12\"]\nmuq = [\"muq==0.1.0\"]\nwav2clip = [\"wav2clip==0.1.0\"]\ntorch-vggish-yamnet = [\"torch-vggish-yamnet==0.2.1\"]\nvllm = [\"vllm>=0.11.1\"]\nmctct = [\"transformers<5\"]  # mctct was removed in transformers 5\nsiglip = [\"sentencepiece>=0.2.0\",\"protobuf>=3.0.0\"]\nqwen-vl = [\"transformers>=4.57.0\", \"qwen-vl-utils>=0.0.14\"]\n\n[dependency-groups]\nlint = [\n    \"ruff==0.14.0\", # locked so we don't get PRs which fail only due to a lint update\n    \"pre-commit>=4.1.0\",\n    \"typos>1\",\n    \"bibtexparser>=1.4.3\", # used for tests/test_citation_formatting.py\n]\ntest = [\n    \"pytest>=8.3.4,<8.4.0\",\n    \"pytest-xdist>=3.6.1,<3.7.0\",\n    \"pytest-coverage>=0.0\",\n    \"pytest-rerunfailures>=15.0,<16.0\",\n    \"iso639>=0.1.4\", # used for tests/scripts/test_generate_model_meta.py\n    \"GitPython>=3.0.0\",\n    \"tabulate>=0.9.0\",\n    \"bibtexparser>=1.4.3\", # used for tests/test_citation_formatting.py\n]\ndocs = [\n    \"zensical>=0.0.11\",\n    \"mkdocstrings-python>=1.18.2\",\n    \"tabulate>=0.9.0\",\n]\ntyping = [\n    \"mypy==1.19.1\",\n    \"ty